      <div class="col-lg-3">
        <h1> Purpose, Program, and Users</h1>
        <p> Libraries are a means for society to distribute information. Traditionally, this information has been through books, but the digital age has brought increased throughput of information in new forms. Highly aware of this, the commissioners of the San Antonio Central Library wanted to create a flexible space for the community to continue to learn as technology changed the ways people learned and interacted with information.(#I) Furthermore, the governing librarians wanted to create an dramatic and welcoming space to attract guests and keep them there.(#I).</p>
        <p> To this end, the San Antonio Central Library has created a number of learning spaces. These spaces revolve around a central six-story atrium to draw guests in, but maintain their orientation in the otherwise confusing building (#I). Areas include:
</p>
        <ul>
          <li> Stacks </li>
          <li> Computer Labs available to the public </li>
          <li> Texana / Genealogy database server housing and access computers </li>
          <li> Low Vision Reading Room </li>
          <li> Music Production Studio </li>
          <li> Terraces for events </li>
          <li> 3D printers, tablets, and training computers in learning labs </li>
          <li> Meeting rooms </li>
        </ul>
        <p> This invites many people to the library, including: </p>
        <ul>
          <li> Readers </li>
          <li> Children </li>
          <li> English learners </li>
          <li> The Visually impaired </li>
          <li> Budding musicians </li>
          <li> Job seekers who apply using the public computers </li>
          <li> Employers who post on the public small business posting boards </li>
          <li> Elderly who are trying to learn how to use computers </li>
          <li> Teenagers who are interested in music, technology, computers, or reading </li>
          <li> Artists, who can display their art </li>
          <li> People interested in their ancestry </li>
          <li> Book Event Attendees </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
