      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h1> Google Earth </h1>
        <div class="row">
          <div class = "col-lg-6">
            <p> The San Antonio Central Library is located in an urban setting, but not too close to the other towers of downtown San Antonio and the river walk. The intersection is indeed awkward, and the parallelogram shape of the building fits well with the streets, aligning each side to some street.
            </p>
            <p> As noticeable as other features, the building is simply different than its surrounding parks, hospitals, schools, parking lots, and other buildings, in terms of color and shape. In this sense, it attempts to impose its own vision on the area, rather than conform to the dominant style. Whether this is a good or bad thing is up to the beholder. </p>
            <p> It is certainly an imposing structure. They even colored the sidewalks. </p>
          </div>
          <div class = "col-lg-6">
            <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
